     "firstPrinciples": "A big client becomes learnable when related operations are grouped. Instead of one giant method list, AIProjectClient exposes named operation groups that match project resource families.",
     "definition": "Current GA reference lists AIProjectClient variables beta, agents, evaluation_rules, connections, datasets, deployments, and indexes. The README also describes OpenAI client access with get_openai_client and evaluation tools through evaluation_rules plus beta evaluation sub-clients. The older or requested names .inference and .evaluations are not listed in the current GA AIProjectClient reference, so treat them as version-sensitive until the exact installed package confirms them.",
     "analogy": "The client is a command center with labeled desks. Agents sit at one desk, connections at another, deployments at another. If a desk was renamed between previews, read the map for the version you installed before giving orders.",
     "mentalModel": "Use dir or hasattr for exploration, but rely on the official reference and changelog for course material. Teach the stable names first and mark preview or renamed surfaces clearly.",
     "diagram": "flowchart TD\nClient[AIProjectClient] --> Agents[agents]\nClient --> Connections[connections]\nClient --> Deployments[deployments]\nClient --> Datasets[datasets]\nClient --> Indexes[indexes]\nClient --> EvalRules[evaluation rules]\nClient --> Beta[beta preview groups]\nClient --> OpenAI[get openai client]",
