     "tags": [
      "async",
      "aio",
      "transport"
     ],
     "firstPrinciples": "Concurrency is about waiting efficiently. A script can block while one request finishes, but a web service or batch worker may need to keep doing other work while many network calls are in flight.",
     "definition": "The synchronous client is azure.ai.projects.AIProjectClient with azure.identity.DefaultAzureCredential. The asynchronous client is azure.ai.projects.aio.AIProjectClient with azure.identity.aio.DefaultAzureCredential and async with. The async reference returns AsyncOpenAI from get_openai_client, and async usage needs an async transport such as aiohttp.",
     "analogy": "Sync is one clerk walking each form to the counter. Async is one dispatcher tracking many forms while the counters work in parallel.",
     "mentalModel": "Use sync for notebooks, CLIs, and simple lessons. Use async when your app already runs asyncio or needs many concurrent network operations.",
     "diagram": "flowchart TD\nSimpleScript[Simple script] --> SyncClient[azure ai projects AIProjectClient]\nAsyncApp[Async app] --> AioClient[azure ai projects aio AIProjectClient]\nAioClient --> AsyncCredential[azure identity aio credential]\nAioClient --> AsyncOpenAI[AsyncOpenAI client]",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "Construct the async project client and print its type.",
      "content": "import asyncio\nimport os\nfrom azure.ai.projects.aio import AIProjectClient\nfrom azure.identity.aio import DefaultAzureCredential\n\nasync def main():\n    async with DefaultAzureCredential() as credential:\n        async with AIProjectClient(\n            endpoint=os.environ[\"FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT\"],\n            credential=credential,\n        ) as project_client:\n            print(type(project_client).__name__)\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n"
     },
