     "id": "cost-mental-model",
     "title": "Cost mental model",
     "term": "Cost model",
     "tags": [
      "cost",
      "billing",
      "paygo",
      "ptu",
      "compute-hours"
     ],
     "firstPrinciples": "Cost follows the scarce thing you consume or reserve: tokens, throughput, or machines. A good deployment plan chooses the cost shape before optimizing exact prices.",
     "definition": "Standard, Global Standard, Data Zone Standard, and serverless-style deployments commonly use pay-per-token or usage billing. Provisioned deployment types charge for reserved PTU capacity. Managed compute charges for VM resources and time, so idle endpoints can still cost money. Exact prices change; the durable mental model is per-token versus reserved throughput versus compute-hours.",
     "analogy": "Pay-per-token is paying per taxi ride. PTU is a monthly reserved lane. Managed compute is leasing the vehicle by the hour.",
     "mentalModel": "Use pay-as-you-go for prototypes and bursty traffic, provisioned for steady high-throughput workloads needing lower latency variance, and managed compute when host control or model support requires it. Watch overallocated TPM, unused PTUs, and idle managed compute.",
     "diagram": "flowchart TD\n  Workload[workload] --> Bursty[bursty]\n  Workload --> Steady[steady high volume]\n  Workload --> Custom[custom host]\n  Bursty --> Tokens[per token]\n  Steady --> PTUCost[reserved PTU]\n  Custom --> Compute[compute hours]",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "Small helper to choose the first cost bucket to estimate.",
      "content": "def choose_cost_model(traffic_pattern, needs_reserved_latency, needs_custom_host):\n    # No prices are embedded; this only selects the billing shape to evaluate.\n    if needs_custom_host:\n        return \"managed compute: VM size * instance count * hours\"\n    if needs_reserved_latency or traffic_pattern == \"steady_high_volume\":\n        return \"provisioned: required PTUs * reservation duration\"\n    return \"standard or serverless: input and output usage such as tokens\"\n\nprint(choose_cost_model(\"bursty\", False, False))\n"
     },
     "drills": [
      {
       "q": "What cost shape fits Global Standard?",
       "a": "Pay-per-token usage billing."
      },
      {
       "q": "What cost shape fits provisioned deployments?",
       "a": "Reserved PTU capacity."
      },
      {
       "q": "What cost shape fits managed compute?",
       "a": "VM resource size, instance count, and running hours."
      }
     ],
     "teachBack": "Cost is a shape before it is a number. Pay-as-you-go follows usage, provisioned follows reserved capacity, and managed compute follows running machines. I pick the shape that matches workload and compliance needs.",
     "glossary": [
      {
       "term": "Pay-per-token",
       "definition": "Usage billing tied to inputs and outputs such as tokens."
      },
      {
       "term": "Reserved capacity",
       "definition": "Capacity paid for ahead of use."
      },
      {
       "term": "Compute-hour",
       "definition": "Billing based on machine resources over time."
      },
      {
       "term": "Idle cost",
       "definition": "Cost incurred when resources run with little traffic."
      }
     ],
