     "firstPrinciples": "A model predicts next tokens with probabilities. Parameters do not change what the model knows; they change how the next-token probability distribution is sampled, constrained, or penalized.",
     "definition": "Core parameters include temperature for randomness, top_p for nucleus sampling, max_tokens for output budget, stop for stop strings, frequency_penalty for reducing repeated tokens, presence_penalty for encouraging new topics, seed for best-effort repeatability, and model for deployment selection.",
     "analogy": "Think of the model as a skilled musician improvising. Temperature controls how adventurous the solo is. max_tokens is the time limit. stop is the conductor's cutoff gesture. Penalties tell the musician not to keep repeating the same riff.",
     "mentalModel": "Change one knob at a time. For deterministic extraction, lower temperature and set max_tokens. For brainstorming, raise temperature modestly. Avoid tuning temperature and top_p together until you can explain the tradeoff.",
     "diagram": "flowchart LR\n  Prompt[Messages] --> Distribution[Next token probabilities]\n  Distribution --> Temp[Temperature]\n  Distribution --> TopP[Top p]\n  Temp --> Sample[Chosen tokens]\n  TopP --> Sample\n  Sample --> Limits[Max tokens and stop]\n  Limits --> Answer[Final answer]",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "One request showing the main generation controls.",
      "content": "import os\nfrom azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential\nfrom azure.ai.inference import ChatCompletionsClient\nfrom azure.ai.inference.models import SystemMessage, UserMessage\n\nclient = ChatCompletionsClient(\n    endpoint=os.environ[\"AZURE_AI_CHAT_ENDPOINT\"],\n    credential=DefaultAzureCredential(),\n)\n\nresponse = client.complete(\n    model=os.getenv(\"AZURE_AI_MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME\"),\n    messages=[\n        SystemMessage(\"Return a practical checklist.\"),\n        UserMessage(\"Checklist for calling a Foundry model safely from code.\"),\n    ],\n    temperature=0.2,          # Lower means more focused and repeatable.\n    max_tokens=250,           # Caps generated output length.\n    top_p=1.0,                # Usually leave at default when tuning temperature.\n    stop=[\"END_OF_CHECKLIST\"],# Stop if this text appears.\n    frequency_penalty=0.0,    # Positive values reduce repeated wording.\n    presence_penalty=0.0,     # Positive values encourage new topics.\n    seed=1234,                # Best effort determinism, not a guarantee.\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)"
     },
