     "firstPrinciples": "Text is flexible but brittle for machines. If downstream code needs fields, the model should be constrained to produce JSON, and your code should still parse and validate it like untrusted input.",
     "definition": "response_format controls output format. The ChatCompletionsClient reference lists 'text', 'json_object', and JsonSchemaFormat. JSON object mode asks the model to emit valid JSON text without a schema; schema mode asks it to follow a supplied schema if supported by the model.",
     "analogy": "Plain text is a paragraph. JSON mode is a form. Schema mode is a form with required boxes and field types. The model can still make mistakes, so your parser is the receiving clerk.",
