     "firstPrinciples": "The response object is your flight recorder. It tells you what the model said, why it stopped, and how many tokens were consumed. Treat it as telemetry, not just a string container.",
     "definition": "A non-streaming complete call returns ChatCompletions. Important fields are choices, each choice's message.content, finish_reason, and response.usage. Usage reports prompt, completion, and total token counts when the service provides them.",
     "analogy": "A restaurant receipt has items, subtotal, and payment status. The model response has content, stop reason, and token bill. If the meal ended early because the kitchen closed, finish_reason helps you notice.",
