     "firstPrinciples": "Without streaming, your user waits until the whole answer exists. With streaming, the service sends small updates as tokens are produced, reducing perceived latency and enabling progress displays.",
     "definition": "ChatCompletionsClient.complete accepts stream=True. The result is an iterable StreamingChatCompletions object. Each update can contain choices[0].delta.content, and some updates may contain usage.",
     "analogy": "A normal response is receiving a finished book. Streaming is watching the author type line by line. You still need to bind the pages together at the end if your application needs the full text.",
     "mentalModel": "Stream for chat UIs, long answers, and progress-sensitive work. Accumulate deltas into a buffer if later code needs the complete answer. Remember that not every streaming event contains content.",
     "diagram": "sequenceDiagram\n  participant App as Python app\n  participant SDK as ChatCompletionsClient\n  participant Service as Inference service\n  participant UI as User interface\n  App->>SDK: complete stream true\n  SDK->>Service: streaming request\n  Service-->>SDK: delta one\n  SDK-->>UI: print token text\n  Service-->>SDK: delta two\n  SDK-->>UI: append token text\n  Service-->>SDK: final usage\n  SDK-->>App: stream ends",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "Consume streaming deltas and assemble the final answer.",
      "content": "import os\nfrom azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential\nfrom azure.ai.inference import ChatCompletionsClient\nfrom azure.ai.inference.models import SystemMessage, UserMessage\n\nclient = ChatCompletionsClient(\n    endpoint=os.environ[\"AZURE_AI_CHAT_ENDPOINT\"],\n    credential=DefaultAzureCredential(),\n)\n\nstream = client.complete(\n    stream=True,\n    model=os.getenv(\"AZURE_AI_MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME\"),\n    messages=[\n        SystemMessage(\"Write in short sentences.\"),\n        UserMessage(\"Teach me what streaming means for LLMs.\"),\n    ],\n)\n\nparts = []\nfor update in stream:\n    if update.choices and update.choices[0].delta:\n        text = update.choices[0].delta.content or \"\"\n        print(text, end=\"\", flush=True)\n        parts.append(text)\n    if update.usage:\n        print(f\"\nusage: {update.usage}\")\n\nfull_answer = \"\".join(parts)\nprint(\"\nreceived characters:\", len(full_answer))"
     },
