     "firstPrinciples": "An embedding converts meaning into coordinates. Similar meanings land near each other in vector space, making search, clustering, recommendations, and retrieval possible.",
     "definition": "EmbeddingsClient calls the embeddings route and returns EmbeddingsResult. The embed method accepts input as a list of strings and can take model, dimensions, encoding_format, input_type, and model_extras. Each response item has an embedding vector and index.",
     "analogy": "If text meaning were a city, an embedding is GPS coordinates. Similar sentences are nearby neighborhoods. A vector database is the map index that finds nearby coordinates quickly.",
     "mentalModel": "Use embeddings for comparison, not for generation. Store vectors with the original text and metadata. At query time, embed the query, retrieve nearest vectors, and pass matching text to chat only if you are building retrieval-augmented generation.",
     "diagram": "flowchart LR\n  Text[Input text] --> Embed[EmbeddingsClient embed]\n  Embed --> Vector[Float vector]\n  Vector --> Store[Vector index]\n  Query[Query text] --> QueryVec[Query vector]\n  QueryVec --> Search[Nearest neighbor search]\n  Store --> Search\n  Search --> Matches[Relevant documents]",
