     "firstPrinciples": "First principles: long work needs a ledger. The user request, the agent decisions, tool calls, results, and final answer must be represented as durable objects so clients can retry, inspect, and audit work.",
     "definition": "In the thread-run model, an Agent is the configured worker, a Thread is the conversation workspace, a Message is a user or assistant entry, a Run is one execution of an agent over a thread, and RunSteps are the detailed actions taken inside that run.",
     "analogy": "A thread is a case file, messages are pages added to the file, a run is assigning the case to the agent, and run steps are the timestamped actions in the case log.",
     "mentalModel": "The object model separates state from execution. You can add messages to a thread, start a run, poll until the run is complete or needs action, then list messages and run steps to understand the result.",
     "diagram": "graph TD\nAgent[Agent config] --> Run[Run]\nThread[Thread state] --> Run\nMessage[User message] --> Thread\nRun --> StepA[Run step model call]\nRun --> StepB[Run step tool call]\nRun --> StepC[Run step final message]",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "Minimal thread run loop using the azure-ai-agents sample surface",
      "content": "# pip install azure-ai-projects azure-ai-agents>=1.2.0b3 azure-identity --pre\n# This shape mirrors Azure SDK samples that expose threads, messages, runs, and run steps.\nimport os, time\nfrom azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential\nfrom azure.ai.projects import AIProjectClient\n\nproject_client = AIProjectClient(\n    endpoint=os.environ[\"PROJECT_ENDPOINT\"],\n    credential=DefaultAzureCredential(),\n)\n\nwith project_client:\n    agents = project_client.agents\n    agent = agents.create_agent(\n        model=os.environ[\"MODEL_DEPLOYMENT_NAME\"],\n        name=\"state-objects-demo\",\n        instructions=\"Answer in one paragraph and cite which tool you used if any.\",\n    )\n    thread = agents.threads.create()\n    agents.messages.create(thread_id=thread.id, role=\"user\", content=\"Explain what a run step is.\")\n    run = agents.runs.create(thread_id=thread.id, agent_id=agent.id)\n\n    while run.status in {\"queued\", \"in_progress\", \"requires_action\"}:\n        time.sleep(1)\n        run = agents.runs.get(thread_id=thread.id, run_id=run.id)\n\n    for step in agents.run_steps.list(thread_id=thread.id, run_id=run.id):\n        print(step.get(\"id\"), step.get(\"status\"), step.get(\"type\"))\n    for message in agents.messages.list(thread_id=thread.id):\n        print(message.role, message.text_messages[-1].text.value if message.text_messages else \"\")\n    agents.delete_agent(agent.id)\n"
     },
