     "firstPrinciples": "First principles: tool-using agents are not a single request-response. The model may need to pause, ask for a tool, wait for approval, receive the result, and only then answer. The client must drive or monitor that state machine safely.",
     "definition": "The run loop is the control flow that creates or reuses conversation state, adds user input, starts a run or response, waits for completion, handles required tool actions such as MCP approvals, and reads the final messages or output text.",
     "analogy": "It is like air traffic control: clear the plane for takeoff, watch status, approve special maneuvers, and log the landing before closing the flight.",
     "mentalModel": "Never assume the first response is final. Check status or output items. If the agent asks for approval or tool output, provide it, then continue the same run or previous response ID.",
     "diagram": "sequenceDiagram\nparticipant User as User\nparticipant App as Client app\nparticipant Agent as Foundry agent\nparticipant MCP as MCP server\nUser->>App: ask question\nApp->>Agent: create thread or conversation\nApp->>Agent: add message and start run\nAgent->>Agent: reason over instructions and state\nAgent-->>App: approval needed for tool\nApp->>App: review tool name and arguments\nApp->>Agent: approve or deny\nAgent->>MCP: call allowed tool\nMCP-->>Agent: tool result\nAgent-->>App: final answer\nApp-->>User: show answer and trace id",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "Responses API run loop with MCP approval items",
      "content": "# pip install azure-ai-projects>=2.0.0 azure-identity openai\n# Uses the current prompt-agent Responses pattern from Microsoft Learn.\nimport json, os\nfrom azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential\nfrom azure.ai.projects import AIProjectClient\nfrom openai.types.responses.response_input_param import McpApprovalResponse\n\nproject = AIProjectClient(endpoint=os.environ[\"PROJECT_ENDPOINT\"], credential=DefaultAzureCredential())\nopenai = project.get_openai_client()\nconversation = openai.conversations.create()\n\nresponse = openai.responses.create(\n    conversation=conversation.id,\n    input=\"Use the attached MCP server to answer with one cited fact.\",\n    extra_body={\"agent_reference\": {\"name\": os.environ[\"AGENT_NAME\"], \"type\": \"agent_reference\"}},\n)\n\napprovals = []\nfor item in response.output:\n    if item.type == \"mcp_approval_request\":\n        print(\"Review MCP call\", item.server_label, getattr(item, \"name\", \"unknown\"))\n        print(json.dumps(getattr(item, \"arguments\", {}), indent=2, default=str))\n        # Production policy belongs here. This demo approves only read style tools by name.\n        tool_name = getattr(item, \"name\", \"\")\n        approve = tool_name.startswith((\"get_\", \"list_\", \"search_\", \"read_\"))\n        approvals.append(McpApprovalResponse(type=\"mcp_approval_response\", approval_request_id=item.id, approve=approve))\n\nif approvals:\n    response = openai.responses.create(\n        previous_response_id=response.id,\n        input=approvals,\n        extra_body={\"agent_reference\": {\"name\": os.environ[\"AGENT_NAME\"], \"type\": \"agent_reference\"}},\n    )\n\nprint(response.output_text)\n"
     },
