     "mentalModel": "Pick the smallest tool that fits. Use Code Interpreter for sandboxed Python, File Search for vector-grounded documents, Function tools for your app code, Bing or web grounding for current public information, OpenAPI or Azure Functions for HTTP and serverless APIs, and MCP when a team wants to expose a reusable multi-tool server to many clients.",
     "diagram": "graph TD\nAgent[Agent] --> BuiltIn[Built in tools]\nBuiltIn --> Code[Code interpreter]\nBuiltIn --> Files[File search]\nBuiltIn --> Web[Web search]\nBuiltIn --> Bing[Bing grounding]\nAgent --> Custom[Custom tools]\nCustom --> Function[Function tools]\nCustom --> OpenAPI[OpenAPI tools]\nCustom --> Functions[Azure Functions]\nCustom --> MCP[MCP servers]",
