     "firstPrinciples": "Most operational questions boil down to seven verbs: filter, select, count, rank, calculate, combine, and sample. A beginner does not need every KQL feature to be useful on day one.",
     "definition": "The practical starter set is where to filter rows, project to select columns, summarize and count to aggregate, top to rank, extend to compute new columns, join to combine tables, take to cap results, and order by to sort. Management commands beginning with a dot, such as .show, inspect metadata rather than regular table rows.",
