     "id": "managed-identity-chain",
     "title": "Managed Identity End to End",
     "term": "managed identity",
     "tags": [
      "identity",
      "no-secrets",
      "rbac"
     ],
     "firstPrinciples": "A secret is a reusable password. A managed identity is a cloud-issued identity that gets short-lived tokens. For agents that query production telemetry, short-lived tokens plus least privilege are the safer primitive.",
     "definition": "In this lane, the identity that runs the Kusto MCP server or Foundry tool host authenticates with DefaultAzureCredential or ManagedIdentityCredential. Azure issues an Entra ID token for ADX; ADX authorizes that identity using Azure RBAC and Kusto database roles. No keys, client secrets, or connection-string secrets are needed.",
     "analogy": "Managed identity is a government ID badge printed by the base every morning. It proves who the workload is today, expires quickly, and can be revoked centrally.",
     "mentalModel": "There are two gates: Azure Resource Manager sees whether the identity can read the cluster resource, and Kusto database security roles decide whether the identity can read tables in a database.",
     "diagram": "sequenceDiagram\n  participant A as Foundry agent\n  participant M as Kusto MCP host\n  participant I as Managed identity\n  participant E as Entra ID\n  participant K as ADX cluster\n  A->>M: request KQL tool\n  M->>I: ask for token\n  I->>E: authenticate workload\n  E-->>M: ADX access token\n  M->>K: query with token\n  K-->>M: table result\n  M-->>A: structured rows",
     "code": {
      "language": "python",
      "caption": "Acquire an ADX token with managed identity only.",
      "content": "import os\nfrom azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential, ManagedIdentityCredential\n\n# For user-assigned managed identity in Azure hosting, set AZURE_CLIENT_ID.\nclient_id = os.getenv(\"AZURE_CLIENT_ID\")\ncredential = (\n    ManagedIdentityCredential(client_id=client_id)\n    if client_id\n    else DefaultAzureCredential(exclude_interactive_browser_credential=True)\n)\n\ntoken = credential.get_token(\"https://kusto.kusto.windows.net/.default\")\nprint(\"Got ADX token that expires at\", token.expires_on)\n"
     },
     "drills": [
      {
       "q": "What replaces a connection-string secret?",
       "a": "A managed identity obtaining short-lived Entra ID tokens."
      },
      {
       "q": "Which credential is convenient in code that runs locally and in Azure?",
       "a": "DefaultAzureCredential, with managed identity used automatically in Azure hosting."
      },
      {
       "q": "What should you use for a specific user-assigned identity?",
       "a": "ManagedIdentityCredential with the managed identity client ID."
      }
     ],
     "teachBack": "Managed identity gives the MCP host a secretless Azure identity. The SDK asks Entra ID for an ADX token. ADX still checks whether that identity has the right resource and database permissions.",
     "glossary": [
      {
       "term": "Managed identity",
       "definition": "An Azure-managed Entra identity assigned to a workload."
      },
      {
       "term": "DefaultAzureCredential",
       "definition": "Azure SDK credential chain that can use developer identity locally and managed identity in Azure."
      },
      {
       "term": "Access token",
       "definition": "Short-lived bearer token issued by Entra ID for a resource audience."
      }
     ],
